back, I realise what this is, what is happening.
His heart is giving out.
His body is too weak to continue.
I shove the photo back into his face. “She’s going to be my new toy,
Ronin. She’s going to suffer, she’s going to be hurt much worse than you
have, and it’s all your fault. You did this. You created this…”
His body starts jerking. Blood starts leaking out of wounds that should
be stitched tight.
And then he slumps, his head lops forward ,and the medic shakes their
head as if I’m too stupid to understand.
“Gone,” they say quietly like it’s a shame, like we should all mourn his
