Saul’s hand grabs my arm, jerking me back.
I raise an eyebrow at the level of insolence. He really thinks he’s in a
position to even touch me?
“I, I promised she wouldn’t be hurt.” he says, wrangling his hands
together.
“Right.” Like he was ever in a position to make such a comment.
“I…” He glances to my brother then back to me. “Look, if you agreed I
could take her, keep her quiet.”
“Excuse me?” I retort.
He shrinks at the tone but the stupid, snivelling fuck continues as if he
thinks he has some leverage here, “I have a place, with a basement, look, I
