Fear that I’ve done something undoable. Something unfixable.
Something truly unforgiveable.
She’s smiling, staring back at me in a way that suggests she’s almost
content to die. And she keeps repeating that same bullshit over and over,
that it’s okay. But it isn’t. It is not okay. How dare she think she’s allowed
to leave me now?
And then she gasps out words I’d never believe. That she’s happy to die,
happy to sacrifice herself for me.
My hands tighten around her bloodied body, my feet slam into the
ground as I run as fast as I can, as desperately as I can to get help. Not even
