But even as the new blood is pumped into her, it can’t replace all the
blood she’s losing out of the wound in her stomach.
“She’s bleeding out.” someone yells, like we can’t see all the blood
dripping from the table.
My fists slam into the glass again. More fury, more desperation, more
pure fucking need drives me to do something. But what can I do? What can
